child's basis was its intrinsic content width. Under squeeze, `.links` couldn't yield enough space, and
the remaining pressure visually crowded the logo into wrapping.

**Fix:** Added `flex: 1 1 0; justify-content: flex-end` to `.links`, and `white-space: nowrap` to `.logo`
as a belt-and-suspenders guard on the container level (in addition to the existing `.logoText` guard).
The tagline is the designated yield point: `min-width: 0` + `-webkit-line-clamp: 2` on `.tagline` allows
it to wrap to two lines while the logo remains single-line at all widths.

**Principle extracted:** See AP-066 (amended). Identity elements are Class 1 (rigid, never wrapped).
Ancillary nav content is Class 2 (yields). The flex model must structurally enforce this hierarchy.

